Quote: Capeweed is found on dry sandy soils and poor open pasture near the sea. ... Botanical name: <i>Cryptostemma calendul</i>a, South Africa. Family: Compositae.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Weeds of Roadsides
Author: TAYLOR
Vol / Page: 35
Edition:
Quote: CAPE WEED (<i>Arctotheca calendula</i>) ... This South Africa plant is well-established [on] the west coast of the North Island. ... [It] grows densely in many regions of Australia, where it is a bad weed of wheat ... It has often been called Cape daisy, but this name rightly belongs to a garden flower.
